<p>During the course of breast cancer routine diagnosis, we often have the impression that we are composing a puzzle in which we assemble both morphological and immunohistochemical pieces.</p>
<p>Certainly one of the most important “pieces” of this puzzle is HER-2, but we would have never thought to find it so well defined as in this case!</p>
